## Eager Loading

### includes

```ruby
# Load association
Article.includes(:user)

# Multiple associations
Article.includes(:user, :category, :tags)

# Nested associations
Article.includes(:user, comments: :user)

# Deep nesting
Article.includes(comments: { user: :profile })
```

### preload

```ruby
# Always uses separate queries (like includes)
Article.preload(:user)
Article.preload(:user, :category)

# When to use preload:
# - When you need separate queries
# - When includes causes complex JOIN
```

### eager_load

```ruby
# Always uses LEFT OUTER JOIN
Article.eager_load(:user)
Article.eager_load(:user, :category)

# When to use eager_load:
# - When you need to filter by association
Article.eager_load(:user).where(users: { active: true })
```

### joins

```ruby
# INNER JOIN (doesn't load association data)
Article.joins(:user)
Article.joins(:user, :category)

# Use for filtering only (doesn't prevent N+1)
Article.joins(:user).where(users: { active: true })

# Nested joins
Article.joins(comments: :user)

# Use with includes when filtering
Article.includes(:user).joins(:category).where(categories: { name: 'Tech' })
```

